The '''NBA Canada Series''' are a series of basketball games featuring [[National Basketball Association]] teams that are played in Canada.

==History==
The first official series started in 2012 although previous preseason games have been played in Canada outside of Toronto before. There was no series in 2017 due to the early start of the season.<ref>[https://www.thestar.com/sports/basketball/2017/08/03/nba-scheduling-change-means-no-canada-series-games-this-fall.html]</ref> Planning for the series was overseen by [[Dan MacKenzie]], vice-president and managing director NBA Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://business.financialpost.com/executive/c-suite/how-the-nba-doubled-basketball-engagement-levels-in-canada-with-only-one-team|title=How the NBA doubled basketball engagement levels in Canada with only one team|last=Ovsey|first=Dan |date=2013-06-05|website=Financial Post|access-date=2019-08-08}}</ref>

